info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 09 at 10:10PM CST until February 10 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM CST THURSDAY... * WHAT...Northwest winds 10 to 20 mph with gusts up to 50 mph. * WHERE...Southern Lake and Southern Cook Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Grand Portage Reservation. * WHEN...Until 3 AM CST Thursday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The area of the strongest winds will be along the Lake Superior shoreline from Silver Bay to Grand Marais. People traveling along Highway 61 will encounter strong crosswinds at times through early Thursday morning.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
